# CODEOWNERS — review routing for AIROM.
#
# GitHub semantics: the LAST matching pattern wins, so the catch-all stays
# first and more specific rules follow it.
#
# AIROM is pre-release (v0.1.0-dev) with a single maintainer, so every path
# currently routes to @Roro1727. The sectioning below encodes where routing
# is DESIGNED to go as the contributor base grows — per-provider rule-pack
# ownership is the whole point of the one-file-per-provider layout.

# ── Default: everything ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*                       @Roro1727

# ── rules/ — the contributor hot zone (ARCHITECTURE.md §4, §6.3, decision D3) ──
# Rule packs are ONE YAML FILE PER PROVIDER precisely so that review can be
# routed per provider with no merge conflicts. When provider maintainer teams
# exist, add entries below the fallback, e.g.:
#
#   /rules/models/openai.yaml            @airomhq/openai-rules
#   /rules/models/anthropic.yaml         @airomhq/anthropic-rules
#   /rules/frameworks/langchain.yaml     @airomhq/langchain-rules
#   /rules/vectordb/qdrant.yaml          @airomhq/qdrant-rules
#
# Actual team entries arrive when maintainers exist; until then all rule-pack
# changes route to the core maintainer. Reminder for reviewers: every rule PR
# must carry >=1 positive and >=1 negative fixture (`airom rules lint`
# enforces this in CI, §6.3).
/rules/                 @Roro1727

# ── pkg/airom/ — the public plugin SDK (§4, decision D5) ─────────────────────
# Semver-guarded surface (apidiff in CI). Changes here are breaking-change-
# sensitive and stay routed to core maintainers even after per-provider teams
# take over rules/.
/pkg/airom/             @Roro1727

# ── The canonical architecture document ──────────────────────────────────────
# docs/ARCHITECTURE.md is the single source of truth; changes to it are
# design decisions, not documentation edits.
/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md   @Roro1727
